The evidence with the title 'Obama's final jobs report marks 75 consecutive months of growth ' says Jan 6, 2017  ... Over two million jobs were created in 2016, but economists believe there's still room for improvement in 2017.  ... And 2015—the height of the economic recovery —last year's numbers put outgoing president Barack Obama ahead of George W. Bush (but behind Bill Clinton) when it comes to job creation. 
